The first chapter General Rules
First Amendment (Purpose)
This agreement aims at providing every necessary service's(sequentes 'service') condition of utilization, procedure, EDISON and user's right, duty, responsible contents etc. that EDISON offer.
Second Amendment (Effect and alteration of terms)
① This agreement is effective only if it is announced through EDISON online service or other proper ways.
② EDISON can change this agreement's content without announcement if there are inevitable situations and the changed content  will only be effective if it is announced like  ① section.
③ A member can ask for member withdrawal if they do not agree with the changed agreement and if he/she keeps on using the service after the effective date of policy, the member is defined as consenter to the new agreement. 
Third Amendment (Rule apart from agreement)
Contents that are not indicated in this agreement follows Framework Act on Telecommunication, Telecommunications Business Act, communication network of information encouragement and other related legislation's rule.
Fourth Amendment (Term definition)
Major terms used in this agreement is illustrated below.
1. General member : Person who made a EDISON service use contract and received an ID.
Nonmember : Person using the service without sign-up
2. System administrator : Person who EDISON appointed to manage general services and administer smoothly
The Second Chapter Conclusion of Service use
Fifth amendment (Validation of utilization contract)
① Users who selected "agree" at the sign-up page are considered as consenter of this agreement. The circumstances are same when the agreement changes and if the user did not agree with the changed agreement, the member cancellation is possible.
② Utilization contract is valid after the agreement of the service use wisher with the contract and the approval from EDISON.

Sixth Amendment (Application for utilization)
People who wants to sign-up as a member to use the service, they have to request by recording prescribed sign-up request form from EDISON.
Seventh Amendment (Approval on application for utilization)
① For utilization application on the sixth amendment, EDISON gives permission in order depending on their request time unless there are special reasons.
② EDISON can deny the utilization application for the following situation and can not get their approval until their problems are solved.
1. When there is no space on service facilities
2. When there is a technological problem
3. Cases when the deny is decided as necessary because of EDISON's situation
③ Denial of the utilization application is possible when EDISON recognized the following cases.
1. When the requester did not request with their own name
2. When the requester used different person's name
3. When the utilization application request's required column are filled untruthfully
4, When the requester's purpose is an offense against public morals and disturbs the stabliilty of a society
5. When utilization application request is incomplete which is decided by EDISON 
④ When the request is reserved or denied because of section ② or section ③,  EDISON has to inform the users about it. However, cases when EDISON can not inform the users because of EDISON's attributable reasons are exception.
Eighth amendment (Protection on personal information)
①EDISON respects and protects members' personal information.
②EDISON is doing its best to protect the received personal information from the service using members. Therefore, the personal information protection policy based on Protection of Communications Secrets Act, Telecommunications Business Act, promotion of information and communication network use, and other related legislations are made up to obey. Detailed information is at EDISON personal information protection policy.
③EDISON collects member information during the process when the members provide information on their application for utilization, community activity, various event participation, and other utilization process, and the member's personal information is only used for the purpose of contractual service illustrated in this agreement 
④EDISON can not share or use the member's information received, because of the service use, commercially without permission to him/herself except for the cases below.
1. If it is necessary for the payment of fee caused by telecommunication service
2. If it is necessary for personal identification for statistics producing process, academic research or marketing research
3. If there is a request from the concerned organs according to related Act and subordinate statute for rhetorical purpose by definite method
4. If there is a special rule for different legislation
5. If there is a request from Korea Communication Standards Commission
⑤EDISON can send a cookie to member's computer through service. Member can refuse the cookie reception or set-up the browser to warn the member when the cookie comes
Ninth amendment (Change in contract)
① Member can always look and edit their information through personal information setting
② Member must edit their information provided in application for utilization online if it has changed, and all the responsibilities due to unchanged information exist to the member
Third Chapter EDISON and member's rights and duty
Tenth amendment (EDISON's duty)
①EDISON has a duty to provide a stable and safe service except for the cases below
1. If the service stop is inevitable because of service equipment maintenance, surveillance test, or construction
2. When the key telecommunications business operator prescribed by Telecommunications Business Act has stopped the service
3. When there is a matter of grave concern about war, incident, nature disaster or similar state of national emergancy
4. If there is a problem for service use because of facilities error or login flood
②EDISON must handle the member's opinion's raised through fixed procedure, and should notice the member about the reason and the schedule for the time required and the schedule
Eleventh amendment (Member's duty)
① Member must obey the relevant Act and subordinate statute, this agreement's rule, operation guide, cautions announced through service, EDISON's announcement, and do not disturb EDISON's business
② Member can not do any promoting profit by using the service and distribute datas that are against law without EDISON's prior consent
③ Member has responsibility on the maintanence of their ID and pin. Member takes total responsibility of all the results occurred because of the usage of his/her ID and pin. Also, he/she must notice EDISON right away when their ID and pin are used without permission of oneself and if they didn't, all the problems occurred because of not noticing EDISON are member's responsibility.
④ Member must not do any service related actions illustrated below.
1. Providing or using information received during service use to others by copying, duplicating, changing, publishing, broadcasting, and other method without EDISON's previous consent 
