①EDISON does not guarantee the accuracy and reliablility of the sent information, data, and fact that the member published through service and does not take responsibility on the losses caused by member's choice on service data.
②EDISON does not take responsibility on the losses caused by the data through service and  the member's expectation of profit earned through service
③EDISON does not have duty to intervene the dispute between members or third person because of the service and has no responsibility to pay for damage done by this dispute.
④ EDISON's responsibility is exempted from errors caused by the member's attributable reason during member's service use.
⑤ If there is a loss to EDISON because of the violation on this agreement by the member, the member who violated this agreement has to compensate all losses and exempt EDISON about the loss.
Thirteenth amendment (Indemnification for damage)
EDISON does not take responsibility on member's losses by service supply from EDISON under any circumstances unless EDISON has made a gross negligence.
Fourteenth amendment (Prohibition of transfer)
Member can not transfer or give the service use authority and other authority on service usage to others and also can not provide authority as a mortgage.
The Fourth Chapter Utilization of Service	
Fifteenth amendment (Service use range)
Member can use the service provided within EDISON site by the ID issued during EDISON sign-up. However, there is exceptions when the related company provides contents separately 
Sixteenth amendment (Providing information)
EDISON can provide various information to the member through announcement and e-mail if the information is necessary for member's service use.
Seventeenth amendment (Contents charge)
①Services produced by EDISON are basically free, but the specified fee has to be paid for the usage of charged services and informations.
② The range and price list will be posted later when using charged information servies.
Eighteenth amendment (Member's post)
EDISON can delete the post upload by member without previous warning if the situation is concluded to the following circumstance
1. If the post is a content insulting or a slander to other member' and third person's rights
2. If the content violates public order and traditional custom
3. If the content is agreed that it colligate crime 
4. If the content infringe EDISON's copyright, third person's copyright, and other rights
5. If the content exceed the capacity of data or time EDISON defined
6. If the content includes pornography or linkage to pornography site
7. If the content encourage illegal duplication or hacking
8. If the advertisement's purpose is profit 
9. If the content does not corresponds to the bulletin board's nature
10. If the content is judged as a violation to other relevant Act and subordinate statute
Nineteenth amendment (Posting's copyright)
The rights about the data appeared at the service is illustrated below.
1. The responsibility and rights for the post stays to the poster and EDISON can not use the post for profit purpose unless there is an agreement from the poster. But, non-profit cases are not like that and EDISON also gets the publication within this service
2. Member can not use the information received from the serivce to sell, manufacture, etc. commercially 
Twentieth amendment (Service hours)
①EDISON opens the service immediately when the member's application for utilization is approved, but EDISON has to post on service or notice the member if the service can not be open because of EDISON's business and technique error. 
② Service usage make it a rule to open year round 24 hours. However, the whole or part of the service can be temporally stopped due to EDISON's business and technical problem and can also be stopped by operation process. For cases like this, EDISON announces it before or after maintanence. 
③EDISON can decide the service hours for each service and for this cases, EDISON announces the alternations.

Twenty first amendment (Service offer stop)
For free service, all or part of the main service can be edited or stopped by EDISON's need and in this case, EDISON notices members through e-mail or internet homepage immediately.
The Chapter Five Contract cancel and restriction on service use

Twenty second amendment (Member withdrawal and use limitation)
① If a member wants to withdraw from the membership, him/herself has to request for member withdrawal to the member information management within EDISON site.
②EDISON can cancel the utilization contract without warning or shut down the corresponding member's service usage for fixed time when the member do the following actions 
1. Actions that violate public rule and traditional custom
2. Actions related to crime
3. Actions or plans on service usage to hinder national development and public interest
4. Illegal usage on others' ID and pin
5. Cases when the registered name is not a real name
6. Actions harming or giving disadvantages to other's right
7. When the same user double registered  with different ID 
8. Actions hindering healthy usage and causing harm to the service
9. Spreading computer virus programs that cause telecommunication facilities' malfunction and destruction
10. Violation on condition of utilization from other related statute that EDISON defined

